        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-05 16:19:30.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nThanks Praveen, can you add a .gitignore to ignore all those testing files at the top level of the project, so they are not dups in multiple places, and delete them from source control?   The files needed for testing can go in a README if needed, etc ..",
        "patchset_number": 6
